leton (naval officer)|Samuel Hambleton]]. Greek Revival.\n*[[Antrim 1844]] (1844), Taneytown, Maryland.  Listed on the National Register of Historic Places,\n\n==Massachusetts==\nThere should be 12:\n*[[Inn on Boltwood]] (), Amherst, Massachusetts. Colonial - Colonial Revival.\n*Founding: [[Fairmont Copley Plaza]] (1912), Boston, Massachusetts. \"derives its name from the great American painter [[John Singleton Copley]] (1738-1774). The hotel's architect, [[Henry Janeway Hardenbergh]], combined French and Venetian Renaissance influences on the building's facade.\" Renaissance Revival.\n*[[Hilton Boston Downtown/Faneuil Hall]] (1928), Boston, Massachusetts.  \"as Boston's first Art Deco skyscraper\".  Try [[Hilton Boston]], [[Hilton Boston Downtown]], [[Hilton Boston Downtown Faneuil Hall]]. Art Deco.\n*[[Omni Parker House, Boston]] (1855), Boston, Massachusetts. Classic Revival.\n*[[XV Beacon]] (), Boston, Massachusetts. Beaux Arts.\n*[[The Kendall Hotel]] (1855), Cambridge, Massachusetts.  Was \"The 1895 firehouse is the oldest building in the [[Kendall Square]] area\". Victorian.\n*[[Concord's Colonial Inn]] (), Concord, Massachusetts. Try [[Colonial Inn]]. Federal.\n*[[Harbor View Hotel of Martha's Vineyard]] (1891), Edgartown, Massachusetts. Shingle Style. (doncram: the only Shingle Style one of all HHAs?)\n*[[Crowne Pointe Historic Inn]] (), Provincetown, Massachusetts.  Also [[Crowne Pointe Historic Inn & Spa]]. Victorian.\n*[[Hawthorne Hotel]] (), Salem, Massachusetts. Colonial Revival.\n*Founding: [[The Red Lion Inn]] (1773), Stockbridge, Massachusetts. Federal.\n*[[Publick House Historic Inn]] (1771), Sturbridge, Massachusetts. Try [[Publick House]] \"opened in 1771 under the leadership of Colonel [[Ebenezer Crafts]] in [[Sturbridge, Massachusetts]].\n\n==Michigan==\n*[[Fort Shelby Hotel|DoubleTree Suites by Hilton Hotel Detroit Downtown - Fort Shelby]] (1917), Detroit, Michigan\n*[[The Inn on Ferry Street]] (), Detroit, Michigan, in [[East Ferry Avenue His